The paper deals with object recognition using convolutional neural networks, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the simplification of the network architecture, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper proposes a new architecture that yields competitive performance, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper introduces a new approach for visualizing features learned by CNNs, which is a topic in natural language processing and computer vision (cs.CL).
